article.headline: Idaho 60, CS-Northridge 56
article.story: LOS ANGELES (AP) -- Tyrone Hayes scored 19 of his 21 points in the second half to lead Idaho to a 60-56 victory over Cal State Northridge Saturday night. Hayes was held to two points in the first half on a pair of free throws, but scored eight points during a 16-0 Idaho run that lasted 5 minutes, 44 seconds midway through the second half and helped the Vandals to a 42-36 lead. Hayes, who was 0-for-2 from the field in the first half, made all seven of his shots in the second half as Idaho (10-13, 6-7 Big West Conference) won for the fifth time in its last six games. Cal State Northridge (9-12, 5-8 Big West) came within one point, 57-56, with 24 seconds left, but Taronis Shepard made two free throws and Hayes added one with seven seconds left to close out the scoring. Davin White led the Matadors with 21 points, and Ian Boylan and Thomas Shewmake scored 10 points apiece. The Matadors led at halftime, 28-20, with nine of the Vandals points coming from the foul line. Idaho made only five of its 20 field goal attempts (20 percent) in the first 20 minutes, but shot 52 percent in the second half, making 12 of 23 attempts.
